cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper is about image segmentation using deep learning models, which is a topic in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various deep learning models and their strengths and challenges, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent networks, visual attention models, and generative models, which are sub-topics in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
